6. Apolloniam] Cicero speaks of C. An- tonius having seven cohorts. There were five legions in Macedonia, of which four came over to Brundisium to M. Antonius. The fifth is not the force of which Cicero here speaks, for he mentions only seven

cohorts (Appian, B. C. iii. c. 43); and Ap- pian says (iii. c. 46) that when Antonius advanced into North Italy he had three Macedonian legions, for the remaining legion had come.
